CANTON, Ohio -- Former coaching greats John Madden and Marv Levy will highlight the list of seven presenters during the Pro Football Hall of Fame induction ceremonies. Madden will present former Oakland Raiders punter Ray Guy. Levy will introduce former Buffalo Bills receiver Andre Reed. Defensive end Michael Strahan chose long-time friend and Fox-TV broadcaster Jay Glazer. The four remaining inductees selected family members as presenters at the ceremony on Aug. 2. Linebacker Derrick Brooks chose his son, Decalon Brooks. Tackle Walter Jones also selected his son, Walterius Jones. Defensive end Claude Humphrey went with his daughter, Cheyenne Humphrey-Robinson. Defensive back Aeneas Williams chose his father, Lawrence Williams.